<p>London’s Metropolitan Police said it is looking into media claims that in 2011 Prince Andrew asked a Met close protection officer to obtain personal information about Virginia Giuffre [bbc.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1]. The allegations, based on leaked emails reported by a British newspaper, are being reviewed by the force and involve a taxpayer-funded bodyguard [scmp.com#1][theguardian.com#1]. The development follows Buckingham Palace’s announcement on Friday that Andrew agreed to relinquish use of the Duke of York and other remaining royal titles; the palace has not commented on the police claims [cbsnews.com#1][scmp.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/ayJtmqc3T8JSvwKimW6utY8qKMSRiTjKEX0jzvxx9Uv5w87SWOtwOyHQ6hRxNnHCTm6Fk8Oiyc2oTj_OY9Q_Q1yYGdytX7ADvLFQLoWqkeU-ynyhDwrYgIMQ3P_IGsl8QL2BdpaUIB24LsES96BLABRtJvli9Ot44uRMnwDbpA' alt='London police said they are reviewing claims involving Prince Andrew and a 2011 request.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Leaked details: Leaked emails cited in reports say Andrew gave his bodyguard Giuffre’s date of birth and a confidential U.S. Social Security number [theguardian.com#1].</li><li>Minister reaction: A UK government minister described the leaked-email allegations as “deeply concerning” when asked about them on Sunday [theguardian.com#1].</li><li>Photo timing: The exchange reportedly occurred just hours before a widely circulated photo of Andrew and Giuffre emerged publicly [theguardian.com#1].</li><li>Alleged motive: Some coverage says the request sought potentially damaging information for a smear effort against Giuffre [abcnews.go.com#1][straitstimes.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Metropolitan Police: The force said it is looking into the newspaper allegations regarding the 2011 request. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c3970mxwz9vo'>BBC News</a>)</li><li>UK government minister: Called the leaked-email allegations “deeply concerning.”. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2025/oct/19/met-prince-andrew-police-bodyguard-information-virginia-giuffre'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Buckingham Palace: Did not immediately respond to requests for comment on the policing claims. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/europe/article/3329595/uks-prince-andrew-asked-police-help-smear-sexual-abuse-accuser-newspaper-says'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.reddit.com/r/worldnews/comments/1oana0l/uks_prince_andrew_asked_police_to_help_smear/'>UK&#x27;s Prince Andrew asked police to help smear sexual abuse accuser, newspaper says</a> - reddit.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c3970mxwz9vo'>Police to look into claims Prince Andrew sought information on accuser</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2025/oct/19/met-prince-andrew-police-bodyguard-information-virginia-giuffre'>Police looking into claims Prince Andrew asked officer to find information on Virginia Giuffre</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/europe/article/3329595/uks-prince-andrew-asked-police-help-smear-sexual-abuse-accuser-newspaper-says'>UK’s Prince Andrew asked police to help smear sex abuse accuser, newspaper says</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/police-prince-andrew-enlisted-officer-dig-dirt-accuser-126657819'>Police looking into whether Prince Andrew enlisted officer to dig up dirt on accuser Giuffre</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/prince-andrew-asked-police-to-dig-up-dirt-on-sexual-abuse-accuser-report-9483303#publisher=newsstand'>Prince Andrew Asked Police To Dig Up Dirt On Sexual Abuse Accuser: Report</a> - ndtv.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/british-police-looking-into-claims-prince-andrew-tried-to-smear-accuser'>British police ‘looking into’ claims Prince Andrew tried to smear accuser</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.